    <item>
      <title>Summer Ends</title>
      <link>https://mlahariya.github.io/writingprojects/poetry_2/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mlahariya.github.io/writingprojects/poetry_2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Summer ends&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sunrays turn incandescent windows &lt;br&gt;
Into yellow iridescent reflections &lt;br&gt;
Of  dried up trees outside&lt;br&gt;
I look down at my feet &lt;br&gt;
And the mats are still wet&lt;br&gt;
From soap water I left behind &lt;br&gt;
Before I left.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve come home, two wooden doors&lt;br&gt;
Door bells and windchimes &lt;br&gt;
Leaves leave these days these trees&lt;br&gt;
Before I come back to see &lt;br&gt;
Spring sprouts from siblings running&lt;br&gt;
Behind one another&lt;br&gt;
Chased by &lt;br&gt;
No one, &lt;br&gt;
But me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Summer ends.&lt;br&gt;
And so does eternity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
